Drawing subplot with pylab¶

In [8]:
pl.subplot(1,2,1) #the contents of the brackets(rows,columns,indexes)
pl.plot(x,y,'r--') #this parameter here determines color and line style
pl.subplot(1,2,2) #the contents of the brackets(rows,columns,indexes)
pl.plot(y,x,'g*-')
pl.show()

Set canva grid and axis range¶

In [46]:
fig,Axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(8,10))
Axes[0].plot(x,x**2,x**3,lw=2)
Axes[0].grid(True)

Axes[1].plot(x,x**2,x,x**3,lw=2)
Axes[1].set_ylim([0,60])
Axes[1].set_xlim([2,5])

Axes[1].grid(True)

2D GRAPHICS¶

In [62]:
n=np.array([1,2,3,4,5])
fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,4,figsize=(16,5))
axes[0].set_title("Scatter plot")
axes[0].scatter(x,x+0.25*np.random.randn(len(x)))

axes[1].set_title("Step")
axes[1].step(n,n**2,lw=5)

axes[2].set_title("bar")
axes[2].bar(n,n**2,align='center',width=0.9,alpha=0.9)

axes[3].set_title("fill_between")
axes[3].fill_between(x,x**2,color="green",alpha=0.9)

Draw histogram¶

In [80]:
n=np.random.randn(1000)
fig,ax=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(10,6))
ax[0].set_title("Default Histogram")
ax[0].hist(n)

ax[1].set_title("Cumulative detailed Histogram")
ax[1].hist(n,cumulative=True,bins=5)
plt.show()

Draw contour image¶

In [82]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.cm as cm #color maps
import matplotlib

delta=0.025
x=np.arange(-3.0,3.0,delta)
y=np.arange(-2.0,2.0,delta)
x,y=np.meshgrid(x,y)
z2=np.exp(-(x-1)**2-(y-1)**2)
z1=np.exp(-x**2-y**2)
z=(z1-z2)*2
print(x)
print(y)
